body:
## Browser DOM Capture: Working Example

Here's a working JavaScript example that extracts structured content (tables, rows, cells, paragraphs, images with text styles) from Google Docs edit page by intercepting `DOCS_modelChunk` — the JSON data Google Docs uses to render the canvas.

### How it works

1. **Intercept `DOCS_modelChunk`** via `addInitScript` — this is the document model assigned to `window.DOCS_modelChunk` before the page app consumes it. It contains the full document structure.

2. **Parse the model** — the chunk contains typed items:
   - `is` / `iss` — text content (insert string / suggested insert string)
   - `ae` / `ase` — attached elements like images (regular / suggested edit)
   - `te` / `ste` — text element positions mapping image IDs to string positions
   - `as` / `sas` — attribute spans for text styles (bold, color, font), paragraph styles, row styles

3. **Control characters in the text stream** define the table structure:
   - `\^P` — table start
   - `\^Q` — table end
   - `\^R` — row start
   - `\^\` — cell boundary
   - `\u000b` — line break within cell
   - `*` at image positions — inline element placeholder

4. **CID-to-URL mapping** is embedded in a `<script>` tag on the edit page as a JSON object mapping content IDs to `docs-images-rt` URLs. These URLs are **publicly accessible** (no auth needed to download).

5. **Suggested edit images** (`ase` type with `s-blob-v1-*` CIDs) are included in the model and the URL mapping — the `/export?format=html` API strips them entirely.

### Key advantages over `/export?format=html`

- Includes suggested edit content and images
- Faithful document structure (the export can split/merge table rows differently)
- Access to text styling (bold, italic, colors, background, font)
- Same data source the editor uses to render the canvas

### Example script

Uses [browser-commander](https://github.com/link-foundation/browser-commander) + Playwright:

```javascript
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';
import { launchBrowser, makeBrowserCommander } from 'browser-commander';

const url = process.argv[2];
const outputDir = process.argv[3] || './output';
fs.mkdirSync(path.join(outputDir, 'images'), { recursive: true });

// Step 1: Intercept DOCS_modelChunk
const { browser, page } = await launchBrowser({
  engine: 'playwright',
  headless: true,
  args: ['--no-sandbox'],
});

await page.addInitScript(() => {
  window.__captured_chunks = [];
  Object.defineProperty(window, 'DOCS_modelChunk', {
    set(val) {
      window.__captured_chunks.push(JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(val)));
      window.__DOCS_modelChunk_latest = val;
    },
    get() { return window.__DOCS_modelChunk_latest; },
    configurable: true,
  });
});

const commander = makeBrowserCommander({ page, verbose: false });
await commander.goto({ url, waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 60000 });
await page.waitForTimeout(8000);

// Step 2: Extract model data
const modelData = await page.evaluate(() => {
  const chunks = window.__captured_chunks;
  const allItems = [];
  for (const c of chunks) if (c.chunk) allItems.push(...c.chunk);
  return {
    texts: allItems.filter(i => i.ty === 'is' || i.ty === 'iss'),
    images: allItems.filter(i => i.ty === 'ae' || i.ty === 'ase'),
    positions: allItems.filter(i => i.ty === 'te' || i.ty === 'ste'),
    styles: allItems.filter(i => i.ty === 'as' || i.ty === 'sas'),
  };
});

// Step 3: Extract CID-to-URL mapping from <script> tags
const cidUrlMap = await page.evaluate(() => {
  const scripts = document.querySelectorAll('script');
  const mapping = {};
  for (const s of scripts) {
    const t = s.textContent || '';
    if (!t.includes('docs-images-rt')) continue;
    const regex = /"([A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,})"\s*:\s*"(https:\/\/docs\.google\.com\/docs-images-rt\/[^"]+)"/g;
    let match;
    while ((match = regex.exec(t)) !== null) {
      mapping[match[1]] = match[2].replace(/\\u003d/g, '=');
    }
  }
  return mapping;
});

await commander.destroy();
await browser.close();

// Step 4: Parse document structure from control characters
let fullText = '';
for (const t of modelData.texts) fullText += t.s;

// Map image positions
const imgPosMap = {};
for (const p of modelData.positions) imgPosMap[p.id] = p.spi;

const imagesByPos = {};
for (const img of modelData.images) {
  const pos = imgPosMap[img.id];
  if (pos === undefined) continue;
  const cid = img.epm?.ee_eo?.i_cid;
  imagesByPos[pos] = {
    cid,
    url: cid ? cidUrlMap[cid] : null,
    width: img.epm?.ee_eo?.i_wth,
    height: img.epm?.ee_eo?.i_ht,
    isSuggestion: img.ty === 'ase',
  };
}

// Parse tables/rows/cells using control chars
// \^P=table start, \^Q=table end, \^R=row start, \^\=cell boundary
const tables = [];
let table = null, row = null, cell = null;

for (let i = 0; i < fullText.length; i++) {
  const ch = fullText.charCodeAt(i);
  if (ch === 0x10) { table = { rows: [] }; continue; }
  if (ch === 0x11) { if (table) tables.push(table); table = null; continue; }
  if (ch === 0x12) { row = { cells: [] }; continue; }
  if (ch === 0x1c) {
    if (cell && row) row.cells.push(cell);
    if (!row && table) { row = { cells: [] }; } // implicit row
    cell = { content: [] };
    continue;
  }
  if (ch === 0x0a && cell) { // newline = end of row's cells
    if (cell) row?.cells.push(cell);
    cell = null;
    if (row) table?.rows.push(row);
    row = null;
    continue;
  }
  if (cell) {
    if (imagesByPos[i]) {
      cell.content.push({ type: 'image', ...imagesByPos[i] });
    } else if (fullText[i] !== '*') {
      // Collect text
      const last = cell.content[cell.content.length - 1];
      if (last?.type === 'text') {
        last.text += fullText[i] === '\u000b' ? '\n' : fullText[i];
      } else {
        cell.content.push({
          type: 'text',
          text: fullText[i] === '\u000b' ? '\n' : fullText[i],
        });
      }
    }
  }
}

// Step 5: Download images and generate output
let imgIdx = 0;
for (const t of tables) for (const r of t.rows) for (const c of r.cells) {
  for (const n of c.content) {
    if (n.type === 'image' && n.url) {
      imgIdx++;
      const resp = await fetch(n.url);
      if (resp.ok) {
        const buf = Buffer.from(await resp.arrayBuffer());
        const ext = buf[0] === 0xff ? 'jpg' : 'png';
        const name = `image-${String(imgIdx).padStart(2,'0')}.${ext}`;
        fs.writeFileSync(path.join(outputDir, 'images', name), buf);
        n.file = `images/${name}`;
      }
    }
  }
}

fs.writeFileSync(path.join(outputDir, 'document.json'), JSON.stringify({ tables }, null, 2));
console.log('Done:', imgIdx, 'images,', tables.length, 'tables');
```

### Dependencies

```bash
npm install browser-commander playwright
npx playwright install chromium
```

### Tested output

Successfully extracts all tables, rows, cells, images (including suggested edits), and text with style information from Google Docs. The `docs-images-rt` URLs are publicly accessible without authentication.
